meta {
  name: Get Referenceable Graphs
  type: http
  seq: 10
}

get {
  url: {{host}}/agent-playground/graphs/:id/referenceable-graphs/
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

params:path {
  id: {{graph_id}}
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

vars:pre-request {
  graph_id: 05fed664-761a-4355-ae8e-fa8616cf8861
}

docs {
  # Get Referenceable Graphs

  Returns graphs whose non-draft versions (active or inactive) can be used as `ref_graph_version` without creating a cycle.

  ## Path Parameters
  - `id`: Current graph UUID (graphs referencing this one are filtered to prevent cycles)

  ## Filter Logic
  1. Excludes the current graph (self)
  2. Excludes graphs with only draft versions (includes active + inactive)
  3. Excludes graphs that would create a reference cycle
  4. Includes both user's graphs and system-wide templates

  ## Response
  ```json
  {
    "status": true,
    "result": {
      "graphs": [
        {
          "id": "graph-uuid-1",
          "name": "Summarizer Pipeline",
          "description": "Reusable summarization graph",
          "is_template": false,
          "versions": [
            {
              "id": "version-uuid-2",
              "version_number": 2,
              "status": "active",
              "exposed_ports": [
                {
                  "id": "port-uuid-1",
                  "display_name": "input_text",
                  "direction": "input",
                  "data_schema": {"type": "string"},
                  "required": true,
                  "default_value": null,
                  "metadata": {}
                },
                {
                  "id": "port-uuid-2",
                  "display_name": "summary",
                  "direction": "output",
                  "data_schema": {"type": "string"},
                  "required": true,
                  "default_value": null,
                  "metadata": {}
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "version-uuid-1",
              "version_number": 1,
              "status": "inactive",
              "exposed_ports": [
                {
                  "id": "port-uuid-3",
                  "display_name": "text",
                  "direction": "input",
                  "data_schema": {"type": "string"},
                  "required": true,
                  "default_value": null,
                  "metadata": {}
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "graph-uuid-2",
          "name": "RAG Template",
          "description": "Standard RAG pipeline template",
          "is_template": true,
          "versions": [
            {
              "id": "version-uuid-3",
              "version_number": 1,
              "status": "active",
              "exposed_ports": [
                {
                  "id": "port-uuid-4",
                  "display_name": "query",
                  "direction": "input",
                  "data_schema": {"type": "string"},
                  "required": true,
                  "default_value": null,
                  "metadata": {}
                },
                {
                  "id": "port-uuid-5",
                  "display_name": "response",
                  "direction": "output",
                  "data_schema": {"type": "string"},
                  "required": true,
                  "default_value": null,
                  "metadata": {}
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  }
  ```

  ## Fields
  - `id`: Graph UUID
  - `name`: Graph display name
  - `description`: Graph description (may be null)
  - `is_template`: Whether this is a system-wide template (true) or user's graph (false)
  - `versions`: Array of non-draft versions (active and inactive), ordered by version number descending
    - `id`: GraphVersion UUID to use as `ref_graph_version_id` for subgraph nodes
    - `version_number`: Version number
    - `status`: Version status ("active" or "inactive")
    - `exposed_ports`: Unconnected ports that form the graph's interface (deduplicated by `display_name`). Each port has `id`, `display_name`, `direction`, `data_schema`, `required`, `default_value`, and `metadata`.

  ## Usage
  Use this endpoint when the user wants to add a subgraph node. Choose a version from the `versions` array and use its `id` as the `ref_graph_version_id` for the subgraph node. Both active and inactive versions can be referenced.
}
